<TITLE> Apologetic Adriano ready to leave Inter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MILAN, Nov 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Inter Milan's Adriano, who has hardly featured in the last two seasons, is ready to leave the Italian champions in the January transfer window. The 25-year-old Brazilian striker's attitude and fitness have been criticised by Inter coach Roberto Mancini amid stories of drinking and all-night parties. Adriano was quoted by local media on Friday saying: "I want a quiet life, I prefer not to remember what's happened. It (the drinking) is a thing I regret and I never want to repeat it". Former club Parma and Premier League side West Ham United were linked with Adriano in August but he decided to stay at San Siro and fight for his place, something he is reconsidering. "Now I am waiting for a decision from the coach and the club. I want to play. It doesn't matter where," he said. AC Milan president Silvio Berlusconi said earlier this week that "there aren't any teams who wouldn't like to have a champion like him" but denied wanting to buy the forward
